How to run this on your computer:
Make a github account here
Download Node.js
Just use the installer lol
Download visual studio code
This is the github repository for letslink
Go to the green dropdown button and download the repository as a zip file
Extract all the content of the zip file into your laptop
On visual studio code, go to file -> open folder -> and the open the letlink folder you extracted
Open a terminal tab on your visual studio code
View → terminal
Type up these things:
Npm install
Npm run dev
After typing npm run dev you should get a localhost link that you can open in your browser and use lets
link!
